Inception is a 2010 science fiction thriller directed by Christopher Nolan, centered on the concept of shared dreaming and subconscious manipulation. The film follows Dom Cobb, a skilled "extractor" who enters people's dreams to steal secrets, as he is offered a chance to have his criminal record erased if he can achieve the nearly impossible task of inceptionâ€”planting an idea in someone's mind without them realizing it. As Cobb assembles a team and dives deeper into complex dream layers, the boundaries between reality and dreams blur, forcing him to confront his own haunting memories and inner guilt. The film is renowned for its intellectual depth, stunning visuals, and its ambiguous ending that continues to spark debate.
